This paper deals with the logical treatment of ordered disjunction, which is a concept used in logic programming to represent preferences. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the translation of ordered disjunction into the logic of Here-and-There, which is related to the sub-category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the properties of the 'x' operator, which is related to the sub-categories of Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Computation and Language (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with the characterization of answer sets, which is related to the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
